#. <section class="sutta" id="sn7.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.22:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga"
msgstr "2. Lay Followers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Khomadussasutta"
msgstr "22. At Khomadussa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.184"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.396"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.22:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati khomadussaṃ nāmaṃ sakyānaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, where they "
"have a town named Khomadussa."

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya khomadussaṃ "
"nigamaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Khomadussa for alms."

# In this sutta I follow my normal practice of translating brahmanagahapatika as a dvanda, following BB’s later style, see his note at AN 4.70. However it is true that in this sutta it would probably make more sense as “brahmin householders”.
msgctxt "sn7.22:1.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena khomadussakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā sabhāyaṃ sannipatitā "
"honti kenacideva karaṇīyena, devo ca ekamekaṃ phusāyati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the brahmins and householders of Khomadussa were gathered "
"in the council hall for some business, while a gentle rain drizzled down."

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena sā sabhā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Then the Buddha approached that council."

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.6"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃsu khomadussakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The brahmins and householders saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.7"
msgid "Disvāna etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "and said:"

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.8"
msgid "“ke ca muṇḍakā samaṇakā, ke ca sabhādhammaṃ jānissantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Who are these shavelings, these fake ascetics? Don’t they understand the "
"council rules?”"

msgctxt "sn7.22:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā khomadussake brāhmaṇagahapatike gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha addressed the brahmins and householders of Khomadussa in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.22:2.1"
msgid "“Nesā sabhā yattha na santi santo,"
msgstr "“If good people are not present it is no true council;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:2.2"
msgid "Santo na te ye na vadanti dhammaṃ;"
msgstr "and those whose speak against principle are not good people."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:2.3"
msgid "Rāgañca dosañca pahāya mohaṃ,"
msgstr "Having given up greed, hate, and delusion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:2.4"
msgid "Dhammaṃ vadantā ca bhavanti santo”ti."
msgstr "speakers of principle are good people.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.22:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, khomadussakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Khomadussa said to the "
"Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn7.22:3.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "sn7.22:3.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "sn7.22:3.4"
msgid ""
"Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn7.22:3.5"
msgid "Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn7.22:3.6"
msgid "Upāsakavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.397"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.1"
msgid "Kasi udayo devahito,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.2"
msgid "Aññataramahāsālaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.3"
msgid "Mānatthaddhaṃ paccanīkaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.4"
msgid "Navakammi kaṭṭhahāraṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.5"
msgid "Mātuposakaṃ bhikkhako,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.6"
msgid "Saṅgāravo ca khomadussena dvādasāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn7.22:4.7"
msgid "Brāhmaṇasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses with Brahmins are complete."
